en_520937_0	The Executive Committee and All Island Working Committee of the SLFP decided today to appoint former presidents and prime ministers for its advisory board.
en_520937_1	It was decided during the party meeting held under the patronage of President Maithripala Sirisena at Ape Gama premises.
en_520937_2	The Executive Committee and All Island Working Committee of the Sri Lanka Freedom Party met this morning under the patronage of President Maithripala Sirisena.
en_520937_3	Many Parliamentarians and Senior Members representing the party were present on the occasion.
en_520937_4	President Maithripala Sirisena was reappointed as the Chairman of the SLFP.
en_520937_5	Professor Rohana Lakshman Piyadasa was appointed as the General Secretary.
en_520937_6	Former President Chandrika Bandaranayaka Kumaranatunga, Former President Mahinda Rajapaksa and Former Prime Minister D.M. Jayaratne were appointed to the Party Advisory Board.
en_520937_7	Former General Secretary Minister Duminda Dissanayake is the new National Organizer.
en_520937_8	Former Minister S.B. Dissanayake has been named to the post of Treasurer.
en_520937_9	11 members have been appointed as the Deputy Chairmen of SLFP.
en_520937_10	8 members have been appointed as new Deputy Secretaries.
en_520937_11	All SLFP Parliamentarians at present, have been appointed to the Central Committee.
en_520937_12	Apart from this, Chairman of the party would make other appointments to the Central Committee in the future.
